There are 10 pieces of uuencoded program. All are headed with ZOOL DEMO in
the subject line. So all those of you who want to kill it can do so. If you
post in reply please use a different heading.

Also included is the .info file for the icon.

When you have all of the pieces, either use cat or AmigaDOS JOIN to put them
together. Then uudecode them and you can run the program. Either click on
the icon or type zool in CLI.

It HASN'T been crunched, I managed only 2.5% compression with Lha, so it didn't
seem worth the hassle.

Zool has been tested on a 3Mb A1500 (B2000 to the Americans), running KS2.04.
I DON'T know if its A3000 compatible.

Please note, Zool uses PAL overscan. If you can do so, boot in PAL.

You need 1Mb +

